President Trump made remarks on January 12, 2021, before heading to Texas and the southern border. He stated that the wall at the border has been completed and may be expanded, and that it has been successful in stopping drugs and illegal immigration. He acknowledged that there seems to be a surge in people attempting to cross the border, but assured that the wall has made a tremendous difference. He emphasized that there should be no violence and criticized the ongoing impeachment as a continuation of a witch hunt, which he believes is causing anger and danger to the country.